<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871104-0057 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Kirby Exploration Co.</HL><DD> 11/04/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> KEX EFH </IN><TEXT>   Kirby Exploration Co. said it hired E.F. Hutton andamp; Co. as investment adviser to explore options for its Kirby Exploration Co. of Texas unit.    The Houston-based oil and gas exploration and production company said it is looking at the possibility of combining the unit with another oil and gas company, or possibly selling the unit. Also based in Houston, the unit has annual sales of $21.5 million, a company spokesman said. Kirby Exploration had 1986 revenue of $64.1 million.    In the first nine months of 1987, the unit had an operating loss of $2.2 million, while Kirby Exploration reported consolidated net income of $5.7 million. </TEXT></DOC>